25 /* ------------------------- Interrupt Number Definition ------------------------ */
26 
27 /**
28  * Interrupt vector numbers
29  */
30 typedef enum {
31 /* ------------------------ Processor Exceptions Numbers ------------------------- */
32  Reset_IRQn = -15, /**< 1 Reset Vector, invoked on Power up and warm reset */
33  NonMaskableInt_IRQn = -14, /**< 2 Non maskable Interrupt, cannot be stopped or preempted */
34  HardFault_IRQn = -13, /**< 3 Hard Fault, all classes of Fault */
35  MemoryManagement_IRQn = -12, /**< 4 Memory Management, MPU mismatch, including Access Violation and No Match */
36  BusFault_IRQn = -11, /**< 5 Bus Fault, Pre-Fetch-, Memory Access Fault, other address/memory related Fault */
37  UsageFault_IRQn = -10, /**< 6 Usage Fault, i.e. Undef Instruction, Illegal State Transition */
38  SVCall_IRQn = -5, /**< 11 System Service Call via SVC instruction */
39  DebugMonitor_IRQn = -4, /**< 12 Debug Monitor */
40  PendSV_IRQn = -2, /**< 14 Pendable request for system service */
41  SysTick_IRQn = -1, /**< 15 System Tick Timer */
42 /* ---------------------- MK20D5 VectorTable ---------------------- */
43  DMA0_IRQn = 0, /**< 16 Direct memory access controller */
44  DMA1_IRQn = 1, /**< 17 Direct memory access controller */
45  DMA2_IRQn = 2, /**< 18 Direct memory access controller */
46  DMA3_IRQn = 3, /**< 19 Direct memory access controller */
47  DMA_Error_IRQn = 4, /**< 20 DMA error interrupt */
48  FTF_Command_IRQn = 6, /**< 22 Flash Memory Interface */
49  FTF_ReadCollision_IRQn = 7, /**< 23 Flash Memory Interface */
50  PMC_IRQn = 8, /**< 24 Power Management Controller */
51  LLWU_IRQn = 9, /**< 25 Low Leakage Wakeup */
52  WDOG_IRQn = 10, /**< 26 External Watchdog Monitor */
53  I2C0_IRQn = 11, /**< 27 Inter-Integrated Circuit */
54  SPI0_IRQn = 12, /**< 28 Serial Peripheral Interface */
55  I2S0_Tx_IRQn = 13, /**< 29 Synchronous Serial Interface */
56  I2S0_Rx_IRQn = 14, /**< 30 Synchronous Serial Interface */
57  UART0_LON_IRQn = 15, /**< 31 Serial Communication Interface */
58  UART0_RX_TX_IRQn = 16, /**< 32 Serial Communication Interface */
59  UART0_ERR_IRQn = 17, /**< 33 Serial Communication Interface */
60  UART1_RX_TX_IRQn = 18, /**< 34 Serial Communication Interface */
61  UART1_ERR_IRQn = 19, /**< 35 Serial Communication Interface */
62  UART2_RX_TX_IRQn = 20, /**< 36 Serial Communication Interface */
63  UART2_ERR_IRQn = 21, /**< 37 Serial Communication Interface */
64  ADC0_IRQn = 22, /**< 38 Analogue to Digital Converter */
65  CMP0_IRQn = 23, /**< 39 High-Speed Comparator */
66  CMP1_IRQn = 24, /**< 40 High-Speed Comparator */
67  FTM0_IRQn = 25, /**< 41 FlexTimer Module */
68  FTM1_IRQn = 26, /**< 42 FlexTimer Module */
69  CMT_IRQn = 27, /**< 43 Carrier Modulator Transmitter */
70  RTC_Alarm_IRQn = 28, /**< 44 Real Time Clock */
71  RTC_Seconds_IRQn = 29, /**< 45 Real Time Clock */
72  PIT0_IRQn = 30, /**< 46 Periodic Interrupt Timer */
73  PIT1_IRQn = 31, /**< 47 Periodic Interrupt Timer */
74  PIT2_IRQn = 32, /**< 48 Periodic Interrupt Timer */
75  PIT3_IRQn = 33, /**< 49 Periodic Interrupt Timer */
76  PDB0_IRQn = 34, /**< 50 Programmable Delay Block */
77  USB0_IRQn = 35, /**< 51 Universal Serial Bus */
78  USBDCD_IRQn = 36, /**< 52 USB Device Charger Detection */
79  TSI0_IRQn = 37, /**< 53 Touch Sense Interface */
80  MCG_IRQn = 38, /**< 54 MCG interrupt */
81  LPTMR0_IRQn = 39, /**< 55 Low Power Timer */
82  PORTA_IRQn = 40, /**< 56 General Purpose Input/Output */
83  PORTB_IRQn = 41, /**< 57 General Purpose Input/Output */
84  PORTC_IRQn = 42, /**< 58 General Purpose Input/Output */
85  PORTD_IRQn = 43, /**< 59 General Purpose Input/Output */
86  PORTE_IRQn = 44, /**< 60 General Purpose Input/Output */
87  SWI_IRQn = 45, /**< 61 Software interrupt */
88 } IRQn_Type;

228 /**
229  * @brief Analog-to-Digital Converter
230  */
231 /**
232 * @addtogroup ADC_structs_GROUP ADC struct
233 * @brief Struct for ADC
234 * @{
235 */
236 typedef struct { /* ADC0 Structure */
237  __IO uint32_t SC1[2]; /**< 0000: Status and Control Register 1 */
238  __IO uint32_t CFG1; /**< 0008: Configuration Register 1 */
239  __IO uint32_t CFG2; /**< 000C: Configuration Register 2 */
240  __I uint32_t R[2]; /**< 0010: Data Result Register */
241  __IO uint32_t CV1; /**< 0018: Compare Value */
242  __IO uint32_t CV2; /**< 001C: Compare Value */
243  __IO uint32_t SC2; /**< 0020: Status and Control Register 2 */
244  __IO uint32_t SC3; /**< 0024: Status and Control Register 3 */
245  __IO uint32_t OFS; /**< 0028: Offset Correction Register */
246  __IO uint32_t PG; /**< 002C: Plus-Side Gain Register */
247  __IO uint32_t MG; /**< 0030: Minus-Side Gain Register */
248  __IO uint32_t CLPD; /**< 0034: Plus-Side General Calibration Value */
249  __IO uint32_t CLPS; /**< 0038: Plus-Side General Calibration Value */
250  __IO uint32_t CLP4; /**< 003C: Plus-Side General Calibration Value */
251  __IO uint32_t CLP3; /**< 0040: Plus-Side General Calibration Value */
252  __IO uint32_t CLP2; /**< 0044: Plus-Side General Calibration Value */
253  __IO uint32_t CLP1; /**< 0048: Plus-Side General Calibration Value */
254  __IO uint32_t CLP0; /**< 004C: Plus-Side General Calibration Value */
255  uint8_t RESERVED_0[4];
256  __IO uint32_t CLMD; /**< 0054: Minus-Side General Calibration Value */
257  __IO uint32_t CLMS; /**< 0058: Minus-Side General Calibration Value */
258  __IO uint32_t CLM4; /**< 005C: Minus-Side General Calibration Value */
259  __IO uint32_t CLM3; /**< 0060: Minus-Side General Calibration Value */
260  __IO uint32_t CLM2; /**< 0064: Minus-Side General Calibration Value */
261  __IO uint32_t CLM1; /**< 0068: Minus-Side General Calibration Value */
262  __IO uint32_t CLM0; /**< 006C: Minus-Side General Calibration Value */
263 } ADC_Type;

823 /**
824  * @brief Cyclic Redundancy Check
825  */
826 /**
827 * @addtogroup CRC_structs_GROUP CRC struct
828 * @brief Struct for CRC
829 * @{
830 */
831 typedef struct { /* CRC0 Structure */
832  union { /**< 0000: (size=0004) */
833  __IO uint32_t DATA; /**< 0000: Data register */
834  struct { /**< 0000: (size=0004) */
835  union { /**< 0000: (size=0002) */
836  __IO uint16_t DATAL; /**< 0000: DATAL register */
837  struct { /**< 0000: (size=0002) */
838  __IO uint8_t DATALL; /**< 0000: DATALL register */
839  __IO uint8_t DATALU; /**< 0001: DATALU register */
840  };
841  };
842  union { /**< 0000: (size=0002) */
843  __IO uint16_t DATAH; /**< 0002: DATAH register */
844  struct { /**< 0000: (size=0002) */
845  __IO uint8_t DATAHL; /**< 0002: DATAHL register */
846  __IO uint8_t DATAHU; /**< 0003: DATAHU register */
847  };
848  };
849  };
850  };
851  union { /**< 0000: (size=0004) */
852  __IO uint32_t GPOLY; /**< 0004: Polynomial register */
853  struct { /**< 0000: (size=0004) */
854  union { /**< 0000: (size=0002) */
855  __IO uint16_t GPOLYL; /**< 0004: GPOLYL register */
856  struct { /**< 0000: (size=0002) */
857  __IO uint8_t GPOLYLL; /**< 0004: GPOLYLL register */
858  __IO uint8_t GPOLYLU; /**< 0005: GPOLYLU register */
859  };
860  };
861  union { /**< 0000: (size=0002) */
862  __IO uint16_t GPOLYH; /**< 0006: GPOLYH register */
863  struct { /**< 0000: (size=0002) */
864  __IO uint8_t GPOLYHL; /**< 0006: GPOLYHL register */
865  __IO uint8_t GPOLYHU; /**< 0007: GPOLYHU register */
866  };
867  };
868  };
869  };
870  union { /**< 0000: (size=0004) */
871  __IO uint32_t CTRL; /**< 0008: Control register */
872  struct { /**< 0000: (size=0004) */
873  uint8_t RESERVED_6[3];
874  __IO uint8_t CTRLHU; /**< 000B: Control register (byte access) */
875  };
876  };
877 } CRC_Type;

1011 /* ================================================================================ */

1013 /**
1014  * @brief Enhanced direct memory access controller
1015  */
1016 /**
1017 * @addtogroup DMA0_structs_GROUP DMA0 struct
1018 * @brief Struct for DMA0
1019 * @{
1020 */
1021 typedef struct { /* DMA0 Structure */
1022  __IO uint32_t CR; /**< 0000: Control Register */
1023  __I uint32_t ES; /**< 0004: Error Status Register */
1024  uint8_t RESERVED_0[4];
1025  __IO uint32_t ERQ; /**< 000C: Enable Request Register */
1026  uint8_t RESERVED_1[4];
1027  __IO uint32_t EEI; /**< 0014: Enable Error Interrupt Register */
1028  __O uint8_t CEEI; /**< 0018: Clear Enable Error Interrupt Register */
1029  __O uint8_t SEEI; /**< 0019: Set Enable Error Interrupt Register */
1030  __O uint8_t CERQ; /**< 001A: Clear Enable Request Register */
1031  __O uint8_t SERQ; /**< 001B: Set Enable Request Register */
1032  __O uint8_t CDNE; /**< 001C: Clear DONE Status Bit Register */
1033  __O uint8_t SSRT; /**< 001D: Set START Bit Register */
1034  __O uint8_t CERR; /**< 001E: Clear Error Register */
1035  __O uint8_t CINT; /**< 001F: Clear Interrupt Request Register */
1036  uint8_t RESERVED_2[4];
1037  __IO uint32_t INT; /**< 0024: Interrupt Request Register */
1038  uint8_t RESERVED_3[4];
1039  __IO uint32_t ERR; /**< 002C: Error Register */
1040  uint8_t RESERVED_4[4];
1041  __I uint32_t HRS; /**< 0034: Hardware Request Status Register */
1042  uint8_t RESERVED_5[200];
1043  __IO uint8_t DCHPRI3; /**< 0100: Channel 3 Priority Register */
1044  __IO uint8_t DCHPRI2; /**< 0101: Channel 2 Priority Register */
1045  __IO uint8_t DCHPRI1; /**< 0102: Channel 1 Priority Register */
1046  __IO uint8_t DCHPRI0; /**< 0103: Channel 0 Priority Register */
1047  uint8_t RESERVED_6[3836];
1048  struct {
1049  __IO uint32_t SADDR; /**< 1000: Source Address */
1050  __IO uint16_t SOFF; /**< 1004: Signed Source Address Offset */
1051  __IO uint16_t ATTR; /**< 1006: Transfer Attributes */
1052  union { /**< 1000: (size=0004) */
1053  __IO uint32_t NBYTES_MLNO; /**< 1008: Minor Byte Count (Minor Loop Disabled) */
1054  __IO uint32_t NBYTES_MLOFFNO; /**< 1008: Signed Minor Loop Offset (Minor Loop Enabled and Offset Disabled) */
1055  __IO uint32_t NBYTES_MLOFFYES; /**< 1008: Signed Minor Loop Offset (Minor Loop and Offset Enabled) */
1056  };
1057  __IO uint32_t SLAST; /**< 100C: Last Source Address Adjustment */
1058  __IO uint32_t DADDR; /**< 1010: Destination Address */
1059  __IO uint16_t DOFF; /**< 1014: Signed Destination Address Offset */
1060  union { /**< 1000: (size=0002) */
1061  __IO uint16_t CITER_ELINKNO; /**< 1016: Current Minor Loop Link, Major Loop Count (Channel Linking Disabled) */
1062  __IO uint16_t CITER_ELINKYES; /**< 1016: Current Minor Loop Link, Major Loop Count (Channel Linking Enabled) */
1063  };
1064  __IO uint32_t DLASTSGA; /**< 1018: Last Destination Address Adjustment/Scatter Gather Address */
1065  __IO uint16_t CSR; /**< 101C: Control and Status */
1066  union { /**< 1000: (size=0002) */
1067  __IO uint16_t BITER_ELINKNO; /**< 101E: Beginning Minor Loop Link, Major Loop Count (Channel Linking Disabled) */
1068  __IO uint16_t BITER_ELINKYES; /**< 101E: Beginning Minor Loop Link, Major Loop Count (Channel Linking Enabled) */
1069  };
1070  } TCD[4]; /**< 1000: (cluster: size=0x0080, 128) */
1071 } DMA_Type;

1074  * @} */ /* End group DMA0_structs_GROUP
1075  */

2910  */
2911 /**
2912 * @addtogroup FTM_structs_GROUP FTM struct
2913 * @brief Struct for FTM
2914 * @{
2915 */
2916 typedef struct { /* FTM1 Structure */
2917  __IO uint32_t SC; /**< 0000: Status and Control */
2918  __IO uint32_t CNT; /**< 0004: Counter */
2919  __IO uint32_t MOD; /**< 0008: Modulo */
2920  struct {
2921  __IO uint32_t CnSC; /**< 000C: Channel Status and Control */
2922  __IO uint32_t CnV; /**< 0010: Channel Value */
2923  } CONTROLS[2]; /**< 000C: (cluster: size=0x0010, 16) */
2924  uint8_t RESERVED_1[48];
2925  __IO uint32_t CNTIN; /**< 004C: Counter Initial Value */
2926  __IO uint32_t STATUS; /**< 0050: Capture and Compare Status */
2927  __IO uint32_t MODE; /**< 0054: Features Mode Selection */
2928  __IO uint32_t SYNC; /**< 0058: Synchronization */
2929  __IO uint32_t OUTINIT; /**< 005C: Initial State for Channels Output */
2930  __IO uint32_t OUTMASK; /**< 0060: Output Mask */
2931  __IO uint32_t COMBINE; /**< 0064: Function for Linked Channels */
2932  __IO uint32_t DEADTIME; /**< 0068: Deadtime Insertion Control */
2933  __IO uint32_t EXTTRIG; /**< 006C: FTM External Trigger */
2934  __IO uint32_t POL; /**< 0070: Channels Polarity */
2935  __IO uint32_t FMS; /**< 0074: Fault Mode Status */
2936  __IO uint32_t FILTER; /**< 0078: Input Capture Filter Control */
2937  __IO uint32_t FLTCTRL; /**< 007C: Fault Control */
2938  __IO uint32_t QDCTRL; /**< 0080: Quadrature Decoder Control and Status */
2939  __IO uint32_t CONF; /**< 0084: Configuration */
2940  __IO uint32_t FLTPOL; /**< 0088: FTM Fault Input Polarity */
2941  __IO uint32_t SYNCONF; /**< 008C: Synchronization Configuration */
2942  __IO uint32_t INVCTRL; /**< 0090: FTM Inverting Control */
2943  __IO uint32_t SWOCTRL; /**< 0094: FTM Software Output Control */
2944  __IO uint32_t PWMLOAD; /**< 0098: FTM PWM Load */
2945 } FTM1_Type;

3689  */

3691 * @addtogroup LLWU_structs_GROUP LLWU struct
3692 * @brief Struct for LLWU
3693 * @{
3694 */
3695 typedef struct { /* LLWU Structure */
3696  union { /**< 0000: (size=0004) */
3697  __IO uint8_t PE[4]; /**< 0000: Pin Enable Register */
3698  struct { /**< 0000: (size=0004) */
3699  __IO uint8_t PE1; /**< 0000: Pin Enable 1 Register */
3700  __IO uint8_t PE2; /**< 0001: Pin Enable 2 Register */
3701  __IO uint8_t PE3; /**< 0002: Pin Enable 3 Register */
3702  __IO uint8_t PE4; /**< 0003: Pin Enable 4 Register */
3703  };
3704  };
3705  __IO uint8_t ME; /**< 0004: Module Enable Register */
3706  union { /**< 0000: (size=0002) */
3707  __IO uint8_t PF[2]; /**< 0005: Pin Flag Register */
3708  struct { /**< 0000: (size=0002) */
3709  __IO uint8_t F1; /**< 0005: Pin Flag 1 Register */
3710  __IO uint8_t F2; /**< 0006: Pin Flag 2 Register */
3711  };
3712  };
3713  union { /**< 0000: (size=0001) */
3714  __I uint8_t F3; /**< 0007: Module Flag 3 Register */
3715  __I uint8_t MF; /**< 0007: Module Flag Register */
3716  };
3717  union { /**< 0000: (size=0002) */
3718  struct { /**< 0000: (size=0002) */
3719  __IO uint8_t FILT1; /**< 0008: Pin Filter 1 register */
3720  __IO uint8_t FILT2; /**< 0009: Pin Filter 2 register */
3721  };
3722  __IO uint8_t FILT[2]; /**< 0008: Pin Filter register */
3723  };
3724  __IO uint8_t RST; /**< 000A: Reset Enable Register */
3725 } LLWU_Type;

5376 typedef struct { /* SIM Structure */
5377  __IO uint32_t SOPT1; /**< 0000: System Options Register 1 */
5378  __IO uint32_t SOPT1CFG; /**< 0004: SOPT1 Configuration Register */
5379  uint8_t RESERVED_0[4092];
5380  __IO uint32_t SOPT2; /**< 1004: System Options Register 2 */
5381  uint8_t RESERVED_1[4];
5382  __IO uint32_t SOPT4; /**< 100C: System Options Register 4 */
5383  __IO uint32_t SOPT5; /**< 1010: System Options Register 5 */
5384  uint8_t RESERVED_2[4];
5385  __IO uint32_t SOPT7; /**< 1018: System Options Register 7 */
5386  uint8_t RESERVED_3[8];
5387  __I uint32_t SDID; /**< 1024: System Device Identification Register */
5388  uint8_t RESERVED_4[12];
5389  __IO uint32_t SCGC4; /**< 1034: System Clock Gating Control Register 4 */
5390  __IO uint32_t SCGC5; /**< 1038: System Clock Gating Control Register 5 */
5391  __IO uint32_t SCGC6; /**< 103C: System Clock Gating Control Register 6 */
5392  __IO uint32_t SCGC7; /**< 1040: System Clock Gating Control Register 7 */
5393  __IO uint32_t CLKDIV1; /**< 1044: System Clock Divider Register 1 */
5394  __IO uint32_t CLKDIV2; /**< 1048: System Clock Divider Register 2 */
5395  __IO uint32_t FCFG1; /**< 104C: Flash Configuration Register 1 */
5396  __I uint32_t FCFG2; /**< 1050: Flash Configuration Register 2 */
5397  __I uint32_t UIDH; /**< 1054: Unique Identification Register High */
5398  __I uint32_t UIDMH; /**< 1058: Unique Identification Register Mid-High */
5399  __I uint32_t UIDML; /**< 105C: Unique Identification Register Mid Low */
5400  __I uint32_t UIDL; /**< 1060: Unique Identification Register Low */
5401 } SIM_Type;

6645  __IO uint8_t ET7816; /**< 001E: 7816 Error Threshold Register */
6646  __IO uint8_t TL7816; /**< 001F: 7816 Transmit Length Register */
6647  uint8_t RESERVED_2;
6648  __IO uint8_t C6; /**< 0021: CEA709.1-B Control Register 6 */
6649  __IO uint8_t PCTH; /**< 0022: CEA709.1-B Packet Cycle Time Counter High */
6650  __IO uint8_t PCTL; /**< 0023: CEA709.1-B Packet Cycle Time Counter Low */
6651  __IO uint8_t B1T; /**< 0024: CEA709.1-B Beta1 Timer */
6652  __IO uint8_t SDTH; /**< 0025: CEA709.1-B Secondary Delay Timer High */
6653  __IO uint8_t SDTL; /**< 0026: CEA709.1-B Secondary Delay Timer Low */
6654  __IO uint8_t PRE; /**< 0027: CEA709.1-B Preamble */
6655  __IO uint8_t TPL; /**< 0028: CEA709.1-B Transmit Packet Length */
6656  __IO uint8_t IE; /**< 0029: CEA709.1-B Interrupt Enable Register */
6657  __IO uint8_t WB; /**< 002A: CEA709.1-B WBASE */
6658  __IO uint8_t S3; /**< 002B: CEA709.1-B Status Register */
6659  __IO uint8_t S4; /**< 002C: CEA709.1-B Status Register */
6660  __I uint8_t RPL; /**< 002D: CEA709.1-B Received Packet Length */
6661  __I uint8_t RPREL; /**< 002E: CEA709.1-B Received Preamble Length */
6662  __IO uint8_t CPW; /**< 002F: CEA709.1-B Collision Pulse Width */
6663  __IO uint8_t RIDT; /**< 0030: CEA709.1-B Receive Indeterminate Time */
6664  __IO uint8_t TIDT; /**< 0031: CEA709.1-B Transmit Indeterminate Time */
6665 } UART_Type;

7172  * @brief Universal Asynchronous Receiver/Transmitter
7173  */
7174 /**

7176 * @brief Struct for UART
7177 * @{
7178 */

7180  __IO uint8_t BDH; /**< 0000: Baud Rate Register: High */
7181  __IO uint8_t BDL; /**< 0001: Baud Rate Register: Low */
7182  __IO uint8_t C1; /**< 0002: Control Register 1 */
7183  __IO uint8_t C2; /**< 0003: Control Register 2 */
7184  __I uint8_t S1; /**< 0004: Status Register 1 */

7189  __IO uint8_t MA2; /**< 0009: Match Address Registers 2 */

7191  __IO uint8_t C5; /**< 000B: Control Register 5 */
7192  __I uint8_t ED; /**< 000C: Extended Data Register */
7193  __IO uint8_t MODEM; /**< 000D: Modem Register */
7194  __IO uint8_t IR; /**< 000E: Infrared Register */
7195  uint8_t RESERVED_0;
7196  __IO uint8_t PFIFO; /**< 0010: FIFO Parameters */
7197  __IO uint8_t CFIFO; /**< 0011: FIFO Control Register */
7198  __IO uint8_t SFIFO; /**< 0012: FIFO Status Register */
7199  __IO uint8_t TWFIFO; /**< 0013: FIFO Transmit Watermark */
7200  __I uint8_t TCFIFO; /**< 0014: FIFO Transmit Count */
7201  __IO uint8_t RWFIFO; /**< 0015: FIFO Receive Watermark */
7202  __I uint8_t RCFIFO; /**< 0016: FIFO Receive Count */
7203 } UART1_Type;
